    <svcsubsec id="s26510.2">
        <title>Description of Engine Electrical Components - Engine Mounted</title>
        <svcproc id="s26510.2.1" graphiccount="1">
            <title>BCS Assembly (Boost Control Solenoid)</title>
            <figure id="s26510.2.2.1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figj09/J09043.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="392px"/>
                <caption>BCS solenoid</caption>
            </figure>
            <para>The BCS is mounted on the inlet elbow. The ECM sends a signal to the BCS assembly. The BCS controls
                the boost pressure to the turbocharger pneumatic actuator. The pneumatic actuator controls the
                turbocharger bypass valve.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
